#- 
#- Welcome, traveller, to your guide to the world! Within, you'll find information of the capitals of the countries of the world! While not a perfect text, with this at your side, you should be able to navigate any country with ease.§0
§0
§0Now, let's get started!
#- --==VARATHIA==--§0
§0Varathia, by population and size, is one of the largest nations in the world. It is a monarchy with a small parliament, and is one of the first to adopt a standard currency, the International Credit.§0
§0
§0Olendor==--§0
§0The capitol of the 
#- country, it is the largest city in the empire. It has natural subdivisions across the city, and you can tell where one begins and one ends rather easily. Notable structures include the Nuktuk statue and the Palace.
#- --==MOLOKA==--§0
§0Moloka is a heavily devout nation based off the society of the same name. They even have a nice, short legend about the forked river near their city, Braxos.§0
§0
§0Braxos==--§0
§0A small city, it is a simply beautiful, if cramped, city. It has
#- one, solid theme that it keeps throughout the city. The most notable thing about the city is not any building, however, but the river just outside, and the tale it has to tell.
#- --==NORLUND==--§0
§0A nation far to the north, Norlund is a true parliamentary monarchy, with a prime minister and king both acting as heads of state. It too has adopted a currency, the krun, and has a booming carrot industry, with fields upon fields of them.
#- Konnin==--§0
§0If you make the treacherous journey across the barren wastes just outside, a difficult task even on horseback, you will be greeted with a pleasant, small city. It has a unified theme, but without the crampedness of Moloka. Notable places
#- include the island castle for its sheer aesthetic and the "Poppy" tavern and inn.
#- --==AMARYLLIS==--§0
§0A country with a large landmass, it is an unfortunate truth that most of it is mountainous. There is no real government, though this is more for lack of description than anarchism. Its capital city shares the country's name. This city
#- certainly has room to grow, and though it has no single unified theme, it is still rather pretty. That being said, however, the only building of true note is the local castle.
#- --==AGOTEP==--§0
§0A country located on a river, the local dictatorship is hostile to visitors like you and I. In trying to visit the city, they stated they were not open for visitation.
#- --==WHEATISTAN==--§0
§0As the name would suggest, Wheatistan is the land of wheat. It is run by a parliament, and is a sizable nation, population and sizewise.§0
§0
§0Wheaton==--§0
§0A sizable city itself, it could be theoretically argued that the city is split
#- in twain between the urban areas and the vast farmlands surrounding. Places of note include the Mall, Parliament and the truly enormous bridge. 
#- --==I.C.O.R.==--§0
§0The Interdimensional Council of Ricks, or ICOR, is a relatively small nation. As the name suggests, it is run by three Ricks in an oligarchy.§0
§0
§0C.O.R.==--§0
§0The Citadel of Ricks is the capitol of ICOR. It is a small town, but like many other
#- small towns, it suffers from not having much of note. However, the land surrouding COR is quite grand, with mountains around almost every flank. The roads are also some of the nicest I've seen.
#- --==Carbon==--§0
§0Carbon is, by far, the most wide-reaching nation in the world, with a colony on almost every landmass. It is a constitutional monarchy. Its capitol shares the name, just tacking "City of " to the front. It is a hodgepodge of buildings, with
#- internal divisions that don't seem to signify anything and seem more randomly placed, were it not for the terrain. The terrain itself is hostile to the eye as well, and the path to the city proper might as well be the diagram of the digestive tract. There
#- is one structure of note, however - the carving in the mountain is that of the King, Patar15.
#- --==The Commune==-- The Commune is a small place based on the river. It is anarcho-communist, and as such has no state or economy. It is run by a pure democracy. The capitol which shares its name is not technologically advanced, and there isn't much to
#- write home about. It is little more than a small town on the river, but perhaps the interest lies in seeing how it will function in coming months.
#- And there you have it, a guide to many of the most major nations in the world, and a few smaller ones. I can only hope this guide will be of use to you in your journeys, despite my likely biased approach to them.§0
§0
§0Happy trails!
#- 